# Naming Conventions

## Context
- Applied when writing any code or documentation in the project
- Applies to all variables, functions, methods, classes, interfaces, and comments

## Requirements
- Always use English for code, comments, and documentation
- Variable names should not end with numbers unless necessary (e.g., when distinguishing similar variables)
- Use descriptive variable/function names that clearly express their purpose
- Prioritize code readability first

## Examples
<example>
// Good
const userProfile = fetchUserData();
function calculateTotalPrice(items, taxRate) {...}

// Go example
func ProcessUserRequest(request UserRequest) Response {...}
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// Bad: non-descriptive name with unnecessary number suffix
const data1 = fetchData();

// Bad: non-English variable name
const 用户数据 = fetchUserData();

// Bad: over-commenting obvious code
// Initialize counter to zero
let counter = 0; // Counter starts at zero
</example>